The Nobel Prize in medicine was received by two American biologists, Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greider, as well as fellow countryman Jack Szostak for research in the field of chromosomes.
The Nobel Prize in Chemistry was received by Israeli Ada Jonath and Americans Venkatraman Ramakrishna and Thomas Steitz for explaining the structure and function of ribosomes.
